# automation-529-overload-not-retried-classifier-gap -- History

## v1.1.0 (2026-06-19)

**Changed by:** ProjectHephaestus automation-loop output.log analysis (issues #1528 / #1536, PRs #1531 / #1537)
**Verification:** verified-ci AND verified end-to-end against a live automation-loop run (issue #1517 → PR #1538)

### What changed
- Added a SECOND, sibling instance of the same structural pattern this skill documents: a transient-failure
  handler wired into one agent-call path but ABSENT from a sibling path that calls the same Claude invoker —
  but for a DIFFERENT failure family (429 session-limit, "resets 5pm") and a DIFFERENT missing path (the
  in-loop PR REVIEW path, not the planner). The detect-quota-then-`wait_until` pattern present in
  `_implement_phase.py` was missing from `_review_phase.py` (catch sites `_run_impl_review_step` and
  `_run_impl_review`) and from `pr_reviewer.py` / `review_validator.py`. With the gap, an exhausted quota
  recorded a synthetic `Verdict=ERROR Grade=F` and IMMEDIATELY re-reviewed, firing ~39 doomed reviewer
  sessions in one hour against a quota that did not reset until 5pm.
- Extended `description` with triggers (5)-(7): synthetic-ERROR-then-immediate-retry against exhausted 429
  quota; sibling path lacking the handler its peer has (audit every sibling path calling the same invoker);
  and a CLI that exits 0 with an `is_error:true` JSON envelope a caller treats as a real result.
- Added three "When to Use" bullets for the 429-reviewer instance, the sibling-path-audit lesson, and the
  exit-0 is_error envelope detection gap.
- Quick Reference: added (4) the SHARED `_handle_reviewer_quota_or_overload(error, *, issue_number, iteration)`
  helper (waits on quota reset / backs off on overload BEFORE returning the INFRA_ERROR sentinel; honors a
  typed `ClaudeUsageCapError.reset_epoch`), and (5) the OPT-IN `raise_for_error_envelope(stdout)` +
  `ClaudeUsageCapError(reset_epoch=...)` (a RuntimeError subclass) approach with the CRITICAL design note that
  it must stay opt-in so it does not break retry-aware callers that inspect `CalledProcessError.stdout`.
- Added Detailed Steps 6-8 (audit every sibling path; wait BEFORE surfacing the sentinel; guard the exit-0
  is_error envelope as a distinct gap) and folded the end-to-end re-validation into step 9.
- Added two Failed Attempts rows: (i) recording ERROR + immediate re-review without `wait_until` (burns
  sessions); (ii) trying to centralize the raise inside `invoke_claude_with_session` (breaks retry-aware
  callers' `CalledProcessError` flows — which is WHY the guard must be opt-in).
- Results & Parameters: added the shared-helper, exit-0 envelope guard, typed-error reset_epoch rows and the
  PR/issue references (#1528/#1531, #1536/#1537), supporting PRs (#1530/#1533/#1535), and the end-to-end loop
  re-validation on issue #1517 (PR #1538, Verdict=GO, zero error lines).
- Added a second "Verified On" row for the 429-reviewer sibling-path fix.
- Bumped version 1.0.0 -> 1.1.0; updated `date` to 2026-06-19; added `history:` frontmatter field; updated the
  Overview table to frame the per-path-recurrence root cause.

### Why
This is a MINOR bump: it adds a new instance/finding of the SAME pattern the skill already documents, not a
rewrite. The key generalizable lesson is reinforced and made explicit: when you find a transient-failure
handler (429/529/timeout) in ONE agent-call path, AUDIT EVERY SIBLING PATH that calls the same invoker — the
gap recurs per-path. And a CLI that exits 0 with an `is_error` JSON envelope is a distinct, easily-missed
detection gap from the non-zero-exit / `CalledProcessError` path. Capturing the 429 instance alongside the
original 529 instance makes the skill a stronger early-warning trigger for the next sibling-path gap.

